title: TikTok Ownership Changes to Larry Ellison - What This Means for Political Content Creators
description:
TikTok Ownership Changes to Larry Ellison - What This Means for Political Content Creators

TikTok ownership officially transfers to Larry Ellison and his family on January 22nd, raising serious concerns for political content creators on the platform. Larry Ellison stands as the largest individual donor to Israeli defense funds globally, a hardcore Zionist alongside his son David Ellison, who recently acquired Skydance, Paramount, and CBS. David Ellison installed Barry Weiss to transform CBS News and 60 Minutes into what critics describe as propaganda outlets mirroring Fox News coverage patterns.

The TikTok ban originated when Jonathan Greenblat identified a "TikTok problem" in December following October 7th events. AIPAC and J Street lobbying groups flooded Congress in early 2024, resulting in overwhelming passage of ban legislation under national security pretenses. The underlying issue centered on videos documenting Gaza Strip conditions reaching massive audiences. Joe Biden signed the TikTok ban into law, and now the platform transfers to Zionist ownership interests.

Political satire creators face account ban warnings as the transition approaches. Content addressing Israeli policy, Gaza coverage, media manipulation, and government propaganda efforts appears targeted for removal. The CBS News transformation under Barry Weiss oversight demonstrates how media properties change under new ownership aligned with specific political interests.
YouTube provides an alternative platform for political commentary, comedy, and news analysis without the same ownership constraints. Creators expect rapid changes to TikTok content policies, widespread account bans, and dramatic shifts in algorithmic promotion once Larry Ellison assumes control. The TikTok story represents broader concerns about media consolidation, censorship, and who controls public discourse in digital spaces.

title: Political Fallout: Jimmy Kimmel Slammed After Criticizing ICE in MinneapolisThe
description:
Political Fallout: Jimmy Kimmel Slammed After Criticizing ICE in MinneapolisThe drama surrounding Jimmy Kimmel did not erupt out of nowhere. It was the result of years of built-up tension finally colliding with the wrong moment, the wrong image, and the wrong national mood. For a long time, Kimmel operated under the assumption that the formula would always protect him. Dress political commentary up as comedy, aim it at the same familiar targets, and trust that applause from the studio audience and praise from Hollywood peers would drown out any backlash. That strategy had worked before. But this time, it failed spectacularly. When his Minneapolis ICE-related comments and the Trump ICE T-shirt stunt hit the airwaves, they landed not as satire but as provocation. Instead of laughs, the reaction was immediate anger. Instead of clever irreverence, viewers saw mockery during a period of real fear and real violence. And once that moment went viral, the consequences moved faster than anyone expected.
What made this situation different was timing. The country was already on edge following the Minneapolis shooting, a moment that carried emotional weight far beyond political alignment. In that environment, Kimmel’s visual gag felt tone-deaf to a massive portion of the audience. It was not just another late-night jab.
